Before the Underkingdom, also known as "the Spires", fell to the duergar and then to the giants, the once powerful Dwarven Kingdom was known as Dornat Murr.

Among many famous weapons and armors, the dwarven guards wielded doule-sided warhammers. One side flat and able to smash their foe, but a pick on the other side to pierce through even the most sturdy of armors. Feared were those hammers who could wreak doom onto the dwarven foes.

Lucky souls can still rarely find one of those masterpieces of dwarven craftsmenship, scattered all over the isles.

Value.value: *grunts* I have a task for highly-skilled adventurers who are up for a deadly mission. It will be no easy journey. She has bested the greatest of warriors and only the most skilled banding together in groups have a chance of survival!
Frostspear. She is a great, ancient white dragon. Her younglings have been terrorizing the mountains since they started filling her cave... They kill without prejudice and take what they want.
Go up the mountain toward the Frostmere to find her cave. Cut down some of her younglings and fight the great beast for us and we'll reward you.
*nods slowly* Aye... That's a scale from the beast. Here, take this. *he offers a large, heavy bag*
...You'll find her cave up in the Frostmere. Just follow this road and take the path up past Chillwick. You'll get there eventually. Remember to bring powerful friends with you.
*nods and glances up at the sky, as if looking for something* ...Been kept at bay a little while, at least. Thanks again.

Bring back a scale of hers so we know you fought her. We'll reward you handsomely for helping the town. And remember to take a party with you. The more skilled they are, the better. She and her spawn are leagues stronger than the usual beasts you'll find here.

Gerald Ralten was in the original group of sailors that helped settle Endir's Point, and one of the hardest working miners. After an unfortunate accident though, he found he could no longer swing the pickaxe like he once did, but he couldn't stand to just sit around and be helpless. 

So he opened his home into a bit of a getaway for thirsty miners... A retreat, if you will. Gerald would provide warm and stiff drinks to clean out the coal from an old miner's throat and shake off the ever-present chill.

The honest miners, not wanting to just mooch off of their well-respected neighbor, paid Gerald for his services, and that's how he got the idea to turn his place into a full-fledged Inn.

Dogma of Valkur: There is nothing more invigorating than challenging the elements. The feel of wind and spray on one's face and the deck pitching beneath one's feet is the greatest feeling in the world. If humankind is to expand its reach, daring men and women must defy the odds and dare the impossible. The thrill of exploration is sweeter than wine or rum. There is always risk, but without risk life is empty. Life is to be lived and damn the consequences. One's loyalties are first to one's mates, then to one's ship, and then to Valkur, who protects all sailors. Rely not on Valkur's hand to always extract you from difficulties, for such is coddling and leads to a lack of challenge and the room to grow. Rather, Valkur helps those actively solving their own problems by helping their plans work.
Here lies Endir, his travels end here.
